## Description
The **Switch **operator allows to define multiple boolean expressions and to link each one of them to different data.

> Note

It is possible to define the above expressions using data coming from different input nodes than the ones that will be returned as output.

## Input
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

Any

The input data that you want to use in the boolean expression, or to return as output

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in...**

Any

N-th input, containing the data that you want to use in the boolean expression or return as output

**out0**

Any

The value defined in the settings, depending on the matched boolean expression

> Warning

Data types linked to **inâ€¦ **inputs must correspond to data types allowed in the particular expression.

## Settings
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- In the **Conditions **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add a boolean expression to the list.

A new condition is added to the list:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the **Condition **field, define the conditional expression that you want to use. In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- In the **Output **column, select the input node linked to the data that you want to output to **out0 **if the expression is true.

-  From the **Output for otherwise **drop-down menu, select the input node linked to the data that you want to output to **out0 **if none of the defined boolean expressions is true.![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add item**) at the bottom of the drop-down menu to add a custom value to the list, then click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to confirm.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

> Tip

To rename an input node or a boolean condition, click on its name to edit it.

To remove an input node or a boolean condition from the list, move your mouse over it and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the **Action **column; for example:

In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Special cases
Case

Behavior

**NULL input (no input)**

The operator considers a NULL input as an empty string. The system logs a warning event.
